1
00:00:10,715 --> 00:00:13,413
I'll do it. Let's give this a try.

2
00:00:13,977 --> 00:00:15,791
I'll try opening my heart to you.

3
00:00:15,973 --> 00:00:17,720
I mean, I'll let you court me.

4
00:00:17,995 --> 00:00:22,568
- Why is the poster a picture of me and you?
- Because I bought the rights to this story.

5
00:00:23,617 --> 00:00:25,380
Hey, what are you doing?

6
00:00:25,568 --> 00:00:26,831
Everyone can see your legs now.

7
00:00:27,960 --> 00:00:29,564
I'll pick you up this evening, okay?

8
00:00:30,342 --> 00:00:31,977
Mm. Go ahead.

9
00:00:32,253 --> 00:00:36,742
- Hey North, I think I'll ask Suer to be my boyfriend.
- Huh?

10
00:00:42,817 --> 00:00:43,782
Hey.

11
00:00:44,524 --> 00:00:45,911
I'm sorry.

12
00:00:46,431 --> 00:00:48,457
I have another urgent job today.

13
00:00:48,900 --> 00:00:50,768
Can you stay with North?

14
00:00:51,506 --> 00:00:52,982
North already left.

15
00:00:53,164 --> 00:00:54,280
His boyfriend came to pick him up.

16
00:00:56,564 --> 00:00:57,844
Then what should we do?

17
00:00:58,448 --> 00:01:00,168
Should I find someone else to come with you?

18
00:01:00,346 --> 00:01:02,808
Hey, it's okay. I can stay by myself.

19
00:01:03,204 --> 00:01:04,580
I'm just worried about you.

20
00:01:07,057 --> 00:01:08,937
I'm worried about you too.

21
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:11,546
But I can handle it.

22
00:01:12,937 --> 00:01:14,444
You take care of yourself too.

23
00:01:14,555 --> 00:01:15,791
Don't get hurt.

24
00:01:17,297 --> 00:01:18,760
Okaaay.

25
00:01:22,213 --> 00:01:23,208
Hey.

26
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:25,222
Hmm?

27
00:01:25,977 --> 00:01:27,333
I love you.

28
00:01:30,413 --> 00:01:31,586
You idiot.

29
00:03:31,660 --> 00:03:35,422
- I think I'll ask Suer to be my boyfriend.
- Huh?

30
00:03:38,951 --> 00:03:41,715
Why are you going to ask him to be your boyfriend?

31
00:03:43,813 --> 00:03:45,200
Let me ask you something first.

32
00:03:45,853 --> 00:03:49,600
What has Suer talked to you about?

33
00:03:50,911 --> 00:03:53,888
- Like if I started liking him yet or something?
- Hm.

34
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:57,973
Not yet. The other day he was still complaining to me,
asking why you didn't like him already.

35
00:03:58,377 --> 00:03:59,875
Or maybe he wasn't dramatic enough.

36
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:03,826
I knew it. He must've thought that.

37
00:04:04,515 --> 00:04:05,711
The thing is,

38
00:04:05,968 --> 00:04:07,795
I'm not really someone who shows my feelings that much.

39
00:04:07,973 --> 00:04:11,302
But honestly, I really like him, North.

40
00:04:12,217 --> 00:04:15,920
You know I've been friends with him for a long time.

41
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,977
But I only saw him as a friend.

42
00:04:20,146 --> 00:04:25,000
And after I found out that he liked me,
everything just changed.

43
00:04:25,457 --> 00:04:26,520
How so?

44
00:04:27,848 --> 00:04:28,880
I...

45
00:04:29,111 --> 00:04:31,062
like the way he cares about me.

46
00:04:31,706 --> 00:04:33,791
And when I looked back,

47
00:04:34,044 --> 00:04:35,728
he's always been like this.

48
00:04:35,982 --> 00:04:37,475
Whether before he confessed,

49
00:04:37,591 --> 00:04:40,137
or before he confessed, he was always like this.

50
00:04:40,684 --> 00:04:41,591
It's just that...

51
00:04:41,964 --> 00:04:43,911
he's more open about it now.

52
00:04:44,808 --> 00:04:47,502
But I'm not counting the fact that he went all out.

53
00:04:48,431 --> 00:04:50,764
I think I like him even more.

54
00:04:51,515 --> 00:04:53,040
Everything he gives me,

55
00:04:53,311 --> 00:04:54,662
it's all good.

56
00:04:55,062 --> 00:04:56,617
Then I thought about it,

57
00:04:56,884 --> 00:04:58,413
and talked to Dan about it.

58
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,302
I think...

59
00:05:02,097 --> 00:05:03,546
I really like him.

60
00:05:05,955 --> 00:05:07,208
All this time,

61
00:05:07,453 --> 00:05:08,773
I've loved him a lot.

62
00:05:09,364 --> 00:05:10,871
I can't live without him.

63
00:05:12,168 --> 00:05:14,511
But I drew a line under the word "friend."

64
00:05:15,764 --> 00:05:19,373
So I never thought of him as anything more than that.

65
00:05:19,688 --> 00:05:20,933
Oh.

66
00:05:21,551 --> 00:05:24,920
It's not that you love him, but you just didn't realize it?

67
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:31,480
No.

68
00:05:32,191 --> 00:05:35,186
North, how do you separate love between

69
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:37,751
a friend and a lover?

70
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:40,800
Hmm, if it were me,

71
00:05:41,573 --> 00:05:43,426
I wouldn't get butterflies around a friend.

72
00:05:44,031 --> 00:05:46,004
I wouldn't want to be close to them,

73
00:05:46,213 --> 00:05:49,417
or want them in my sight all the time.

74
00:05:50,582 --> 00:05:52,186
And another thing is,

75
00:05:52,471 --> 00:05:54,368
I wouldn't want to keep them all to myself.

76
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:55,897
Yeah, right?

77
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:58,346
At first, I thought that too.

78
00:05:58,737 --> 00:06:01,386
I even wanted him to have a girlfriend.

79
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:06,920
- That means I only saw him as a friend, right?
- Mm-hm, exactly.

80
00:06:08,380 --> 00:06:10,137
So that means you...

81
00:06:10,586 --> 00:06:12,066
are starting to like him, right?

82
00:06:12,853 --> 00:06:13,822
Yeah.

83
00:06:14,893 --> 00:06:17,302
And I keep liking him more and more.

84
00:06:17,835 --> 00:06:18,977
Until now,

85
00:06:19,328 --> 00:06:20,506
I think...

86
00:06:21,951 --> 00:06:23,293
I love him.

87
00:06:23,751 --> 00:06:26,200
As someone I want to spend my life with.

88
00:06:39,368 --> 00:06:40,697
Shit.

89
00:06:45,022 --> 00:06:46,093
Sorry.

90
00:06:47,106 --> 00:06:49,902
Whenever something gets close to me, I wake up.

91
00:06:52,186 --> 00:06:53,715
Being a mafia member,

92
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:56,457
you have to stay alert all the time, right?

93
00:06:58,653 --> 00:06:59,613
Well...

94
00:06:59,897 --> 00:07:02,613
Why aren't you sleeping? Does your head hurt?

95
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:04,035
Or are you hungry?

96
00:07:14,782 --> 00:07:15,822
Suer.

97
00:07:18,711 --> 00:07:19,800
I love you.

98
00:07:26,026 --> 00:07:27,217
Could you be my boyfriend.

99
00:07:36,297 --> 00:07:37,417
Suer.

100
00:07:37,613 --> 00:07:39,777
Hey, Suer.

101
00:07:40,004 --> 00:07:41,275
Hey.

102
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:47,382
Suer, don’t get into anything bad.

103
00:07:47,528 --> 00:07:48,888
Is he badly hurt?

104
00:07:50,004 --> 00:07:53,386
I don't know. We were just talking and he suddenly passed out.

105
00:07:54,306 --> 00:07:55,862
I think it's because of his work.

106
00:07:56,764 --> 00:07:58,768
But he doesn't have any bleeding.

107
00:07:58,906 --> 00:08:01,440
- Exactly.
- Maybe he's just exhausted.

108
00:08:01,582 --> 00:08:03,235
Or maybe something hit him really hard.

109
00:08:03,555 --> 00:08:04,848
And the symptoms showed up later.

110
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:09,488
I told you to be careful.

111
00:08:09,946 --> 00:08:11,720
Why don't you ever listen?

112
00:08:17,355 --> 00:08:23,057
According to the doctor's examination, the patient doesn't have any abnormal symptoms.
There's nothing to worry about.

113
00:08:23,493 --> 00:08:26,453
Don't worry. He'll recover after getting some rest.

114
00:08:27,497 --> 00:08:28,200
Thank you.

115
00:08:36,173 --> 00:08:38,240
What do you think caused this?

116
00:08:39,684 --> 00:08:40,555
No idea.

117
00:08:41,431 --> 00:08:43,315
But the nurse said that

118
00:08:43,435 --> 00:08:45,848
after some rest, he should wake up soon.

119
00:08:47,488 --> 00:08:49,933
You're sick too, aren't you? Why don't you rest first?

120
00:08:50,151 --> 00:08:51,466
No.

121
00:08:51,795 --> 00:08:54,377
I'm afraid he'll wake up and not see me here.

122
00:09:01,213 --> 00:09:02,328
Hey, hey.

123
00:09:03,302 --> 00:09:04,693
Hey, he's awake.

124
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:07,511
Hey.

125
00:09:08,595 --> 00:09:10,080
You're sick, so why aren't you sleeping?

126
00:09:10,453 --> 00:09:12,840
You're the one who's sick, Suer.

127
00:09:17,862 --> 00:09:19,644
- What's wrong with me?
- I don't know.

128
00:09:19,871 --> 00:09:21,728
We were talking and you suddenly passed out.

129
00:09:29,662 --> 00:09:31,093
Um...

130
00:09:31,546 --> 00:09:34,040
Did you say something before this?

131
00:09:35,302 --> 00:09:36,946
Before you passed out?

132
00:09:37,088 --> 00:09:37,831
Yeah.

133
00:09:38,008 --> 00:09:39,320
Be my boyfriend.

134
00:09:39,995 --> 00:09:40,835
Why?

135
00:09:44,066 --> 00:09:46,297
Suer, don't tell me...

136
00:09:46,471 --> 00:09:48,217
the reason you suddenly passed out was because of that?

137
00:09:49,622 --> 00:09:50,426
Yes.

138
00:09:53,155 --> 00:09:54,168
Idiot.

139
00:09:54,328 --> 00:09:56,288
Why would you even admit it?

140
00:09:58,657 --> 00:09:59,875
No.

141
00:10:00,315 --> 00:10:01,902
My "yes" meant...

142
00:10:03,195 --> 00:10:04,391
I meant yes to becoming your boyfriend.

143
00:10:12,893 --> 00:10:13,982
Yes.

144
00:10:14,773 --> 00:10:15,890
Let's be together.

145
00:10:17,751 --> 00:10:19,844
I love you. Come here.

146
00:10:28,764 --> 00:10:29,862
Idiot.

147
00:10:32,715 --> 00:10:34,617
Since there's nothing else, I'll head back first.

148
00:10:34,795 --> 00:10:36,204
Yeah, I'll go too.

149
00:10:37,466 --> 00:10:39,680
Idiot. Look at you smiling.

150
00:10:40,820 --> 00:10:42,070
Get home safely.

151
00:10:46,195 --> 00:10:48,057
You can let go now.

152
00:10:48,226 --> 00:10:49,315
Suer.

153
00:10:50,315 --> 00:10:52,097
I'm just happy.

154
00:10:52,702 --> 00:10:53,911
Is this real?

155
00:10:54,671 --> 00:10:55,635
Mm.

156
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:58,017
I'm your boyfriend now.

157
00:10:59,111 --> 00:11:00,222
Yeah.

158
00:11:00,746 --> 00:11:01,977
You know?

159
00:11:03,653 --> 00:11:04,893
Exactly.

160
00:11:05,017 --> 00:11:05,977
We're together now.

161
00:11:08,608 --> 00:11:09,680
Come here.

162
00:11:13,137 --> 00:11:15,400
Who cares if we're in a hospital?

163
00:11:20,786 --> 00:11:22,622
So you're really not seriously hurt, right?

164
00:11:23,524 --> 00:11:24,546
Mm.

165
00:11:24,964 --> 00:11:26,253
What could happen to me?

166
00:11:27,820 --> 00:11:29,973
You just passed out because I asked you to be your boyfriend.

167
00:11:31,435 --> 00:11:33,022
I was just shocked.

168
00:11:33,142 --> 00:11:35,084
Who wouldn't be shocked?

169
00:11:35,724 --> 00:11:39,511
So what made you like me?

170
00:11:41,262 --> 00:11:43,955
I mean, I went all out for you so many times.

171
00:11:44,231 --> 00:11:45,684
I thought it still wasn't enough.

172
00:11:47,275 --> 00:11:48,440
The point is,

173
00:11:48,688 --> 00:11:50,382
it's not about how big your gestures are.

174
00:11:50,675 --> 00:11:51,702
I...

175
00:11:52,217 --> 00:11:54,364
like how you take care of me every day.

176
00:11:57,146 --> 00:11:59,062
Then it's not a big deal at all.

177
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:01,684
You even cook for me too.

178
00:12:02,466 --> 00:12:04,560
I know you...

179
00:12:04,920 --> 00:12:08,066
call my mom every day because you really care.

180
00:12:08,293 --> 00:12:10,426
She even made you her favorite student now.

181
00:12:16,484 --> 00:12:19,848
And the movie I made for you... you didn't like it?

182
00:12:21,697 --> 00:12:23,168
I told you already.

183
00:12:23,893 --> 00:12:26,960
I like simple, ordinary things.

184
00:12:27,088 --> 00:12:30,146
But there's nothing ordinary about how cute you are.

185
00:12:37,897 --> 00:12:38,964
Do you love me?

186
00:12:40,164 --> 00:12:43,200
- Why are you asking?
- Answer quickly. I want to know.

187
00:12:46,220 --> 00:12:47,631
Do you love me?

188
00:12:48,031 --> 00:12:48,928
I do.

189
00:12:49,902 --> 00:12:51,435
Do you love me a lot?

190
00:12:54,060 --> 00:12:55,940
- A lot.
- Really that much?

191
00:12:56,226 --> 00:12:57,995
At first, I thought...

192
00:12:58,320 --> 00:12:59,635
you just had a crush on me,

193
00:12:59,860 --> 00:13:01,582
or maybe only liked me a little.

194
00:13:05,995 --> 00:13:07,128
I know now.

195
00:13:07,324 --> 00:13:08,275
That's enough.

196
00:13:21,702 --> 00:13:22,564
What?

197
00:13:25,213 --> 00:13:26,293
Hey.

198
00:13:26,933 --> 00:13:28,546
Are you streaming a game today?

199
00:13:29,008 --> 00:13:30,048
Streaming a game?

200
00:13:31,728 --> 00:13:32,546
Sounds good.

201
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:34,560
I'm going to lose all my fans at this rate.

202
00:13:34,991 --> 00:13:36,528
They won't leave.

203
00:13:37,235 --> 00:13:38,528
At least there's one person.

204
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:41,800
Who?

205
00:13:43,817 --> 00:13:45,195
And how do you even know that?

206
00:13:45,857 --> 00:13:46,595
Well...

207
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:49,200
that regular donor of yours.

208
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:52,351
The one who always donates?

209
00:13:53,377 --> 00:13:56,115
Oh, P'Gun.

210
00:13:56,700 --> 00:13:58,390
Or was it P'Guitar?

211
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:04,222
That second guy is probably dead by now.

212
00:14:04,333 --> 00:14:06,500
- What did you just say?
- Nothing.

213
00:14:07,764 --> 00:14:10,026
Then just go stream.

214
00:14:10,420 --> 00:14:11,271
I'll watch.

215
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:13,720
Okay.

216
00:14:15,248 --> 00:14:17,240
Hello everyone.

217
00:14:17,697 --> 00:14:19,040
So what game are you playing?

218
00:14:19,817 --> 00:14:21,657
Uh... what should I play?

219
00:14:23,573 --> 00:14:24,684
Same game as before.

220
00:14:28,284 --> 00:14:29,857
Aren't you really going to play?

221
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:32,288
I'd rather watch you play.

222
00:14:33,173 --> 00:14:34,488
Mm, okay.

223
00:14:36,928 --> 00:14:39,573
What are you two to each other?

224
00:14:39,915 --> 00:14:41,280
We're dating.

225
00:14:45,164 --> 00:14:47,160
I thought you already were.

226
00:14:47,324 --> 00:14:51,580
And those two guys who were trying to hit on Duennao?
I'm a little sad,

227
00:14:51,653 --> 00:14:54,613
but I'm happier for you both.

228
00:14:55,351 --> 00:14:59,466
If it's those two accounts... the one named Guitar,

229
00:15:00,422 --> 00:15:01,955
I already banned him.

230
00:15:03,533 --> 00:15:05,604
And the other account...

231
00:15:06,444 --> 00:15:07,644
I love you.

232
00:15:10,613 --> 00:15:11,697
It was me.

233
00:15:13,800 --> 00:15:15,680
I've liked Duennao for a long time.

234
00:15:15,782 --> 00:15:17,648
So I was the one donating.

235
00:15:19,088 --> 00:15:20,240
You're serious?

236
00:15:21,511 --> 00:15:22,280
Mm.

237
00:15:25,431 --> 00:15:28,186
I've been trying to get your attention this whole time.

238
00:15:28,328 --> 00:15:30,133
When you called me P'Gun...

239
00:15:30,386 --> 00:15:31,928
I was so blushed.

240
00:15:34,555 --> 00:15:35,875
Are you mad?

241
00:15:37,040 --> 00:15:39,462
I'm not mad at you. It's nothing.

242
00:15:40,044 --> 00:15:41,462
But I'm hurt.

243
00:15:41,657 --> 00:15:43,475
I've been calling you "P' all this time.

244
00:15:44,137 --> 00:15:46,293
Even though I'm actually older than you.

245
00:15:46,460 --> 00:15:47,684
I'm your boyfriend.

246
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:51,880
You idiot.

247
00:15:52,004 --> 00:15:53,240
No, I'm going to play now.

248
00:15:53,297 --> 00:15:54,942
- Don't let go.
- Suer.

249
00:15:55,017 --> 00:15:58,220
No, I won't. No way.

250
00:16:24,328 --> 00:16:26,853
Who are those flowers for, sir?

251
00:16:29,764 --> 00:16:32,257
For the most beautiful person in this bar.

252
00:16:44,071 --> 00:16:47,355
Are you relieved there’s no ring on my finger?

253
00:16:51,395 --> 00:16:52,724
What would you like to drink?

254
00:16:55,631 --> 00:16:56,840
The usual.

255
00:16:57,702 --> 00:16:59,915
And what do you usually like?

256
00:17:02,208 --> 00:17:04,111
- Well...
- Hey, Luke.

257
00:17:04,942 --> 00:17:06,253
You're early today.

258
00:17:06,617 --> 00:17:10,466
- The usual?
- The usual. You really know me so well, Ben.

259
00:17:10,786 --> 00:17:12,822
Why do you know his order but not mine?

260
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:21,764
Ben.

261
00:17:26,340 --> 00:17:28,768
How was your trip to Bangkok?

262
00:17:29,080 --> 00:17:31,071
It was brilliant, Ben.

263
00:17:31,346 --> 00:17:36,297
The people were kind, the temples were beautiful. I had so much fun.

264
00:17:38,924 --> 00:17:40,822
Every second you ignore me,

265
00:17:41,142 --> 00:17:43,022
I'll kill one person in here.

266
00:17:46,511 --> 00:17:48,737
Don't bring that kind of attitude here.

267
00:17:52,048 --> 00:17:53,440
You're talking to me now, aren't you?

268
00:17:55,137 --> 00:17:56,760
You know me.

269
00:17:57,951 --> 00:17:58,982
You do know,

270
00:18:01,311 --> 00:18:03,208
give me what I want.

271
00:18:26,666 --> 00:18:27,897
Are you two close?

272
00:18:29,804 --> 00:18:30,977
Regular customer.

273
00:18:35,417 --> 00:18:36,493
He likes you.

274
00:18:40,240 --> 00:18:42,724
I can tell from the way he looks at you.

275
00:18:45,582 --> 00:18:46,937
What does that have to do with you?

276
00:18:49,373 --> 00:18:50,440
Why wouldn't it?

277
00:18:51,377 --> 00:18:52,951
You want an answer, don't you?

278
00:18:54,173 --> 00:18:55,680
I already gave you one.

279
00:18:57,182 --> 00:18:58,355
Too late.

280
00:19:00,733 --> 00:19:01,928
Honestly, Ben,

281
00:19:02,773 --> 00:19:04,231
you're pretty cruel too.

282
00:19:05,488 --> 00:19:08,537
- Why?
- You know I never cared about love that much.

283
00:19:10,168 --> 00:19:12,475
I only ever saw you as a friend.

284
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:17,506
But suddenly you said it out loud and ran off to New Zealand.

285
00:19:18,060 --> 00:19:20,020
Then you said it was too late. What the hell?

286
00:19:24,257 --> 00:19:25,768
Did you ever think about it?

287
00:19:27,084 --> 00:19:29,111
You were the one coming at me.

288
00:19:29,462 --> 00:19:32,826
- Why didn't you give me time to think?
- I told you, you were married.

289
00:19:32,990 --> 00:19:35,582
- Were you supposed to wait until I got married?
- I didn't marry anyone.

290
00:19:35,582 --> 00:19:38,053
You never said you weren't going to.

291
00:19:38,050 --> 00:19:41,071
- Mr. Ben, a customer wants to see the owner.
- Yes.

292
00:19:41,071 --> 00:19:43,540
There's a problem with insects in the drink.

293
00:19:43,540 --> 00:19:45,500
Alright, I'll take care of it.

294
00:19:57,817 --> 00:19:59,657
Is there a problem, sir?

295
00:20:00,755 --> 00:20:03,804
There's a bug in my drink. You call this acceptable?

296
00:20:05,288 --> 00:20:06,684
What should I do about it?

297
00:20:07,053 --> 00:20:09,786
We'll remake you a new one. Sorry about that.

298
00:20:10,168 --> 00:20:12,980
- Your drinks are free tonight.
- Ben.

299
00:20:13,360 --> 00:20:15,150
Why do you keep refusing me?

300
00:20:15,902 --> 00:20:18,084
You do know I can shut this place down, right?

301
00:20:19,035 --> 00:20:20,044
But, Ben

302
00:20:24,271 --> 00:20:25,500
If you were mine,

303
00:20:26,244 --> 00:20:28,560
your business will definitely thrive again.

304
00:20:30,620 --> 00:20:32,435
Come sit and talk.

305
00:20:34,204 --> 00:20:36,120
Stop it. Stop.

306
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,431
Get him out of here.

307
00:20:47,231 --> 00:20:48,511
The flowers are yours.

308
00:21:17,404 --> 00:21:18,515
I’m sorry.

309
00:21:23,368 --> 00:21:24,755
Please don’t be mad at me.

310
00:21:28,600 --> 00:21:29,751
Are you mad at me?

311
00:21:30,502 --> 00:21:32,288
No, I’m not mad.

312
00:21:36,226 --> 00:21:37,040
Then…

313
00:21:37,537 --> 00:21:39,220
what happened to the guy

314
00:21:40,102 --> 00:21:42,084
who pulled a gun earlier tonight?

315
00:21:45,577 --> 00:21:46,640
He’s gone.

316
00:21:48,511 --> 00:21:51,115
I’ll bring him out again if someone bothers you.

317
00:21:53,204 --> 00:21:54,515
Do you have two personalities or what?

318
00:21:56,195 --> 00:21:57,088
- Ben.
- Singha.

319
00:21:57,915 --> 00:21:59,115
- You go first.
- You talk first.

320
00:22:00,368 --> 00:22:01,342
You talk first

321
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:08,137
Is it pretty?

322
00:22:12,133 --> 00:22:13,435
The flowers are pretty.

323
00:22:13,795 --> 00:22:15,542
- But I don’t—.
- I miss you.

324
00:22:19,306 --> 00:22:21,493
You know I can’t live without you, Ben

325
00:22:25,111 --> 00:22:26,800
You’re everything to me.

326
00:22:28,893 --> 00:22:31,226
Without you, I can’t do anything.

327
00:22:33,897 --> 00:22:37,244
Even picking clothes in the morning—I can’t do it.

328
00:22:39,980 --> 00:22:42,328
I don’t even know what watch matches my outfit.

329
00:22:47,924 --> 00:22:49,400
I don’t even have anyone to help me work.

330
00:22:51,195 --> 00:22:53,324
I’ve messed up work so many times.

331
00:22:55,551 --> 00:22:59,448
- I don’t think you’re that bad.
- I’m just distracted.

332
00:23:00,755 --> 00:23:01,915
Distracted by what?

333
00:23:03,280 --> 00:23:04,991
I miss you, Ben.

334
00:23:09,422 --> 00:23:11,133
When I knew you had someone new,

335
00:23:11,862 --> 00:23:13,300
I can’t stay calm anymore.

336
00:23:16,217 --> 00:23:21,746
Is this jealousy, wanting to keep you for myself… still just “friendship”?

337
00:23:23,502 --> 00:23:24,720
Noใ

338
00:23:26,040 --> 00:23:27,826
You love me, Singha.

339
00:23:29,306 --> 00:23:30,715
You love me.

340
00:24:05,893 --> 00:24:07,968
Your father won’t say anything if you don’t marry?

341
00:24:12,186 --> 00:24:13,471
My father is dead.

342
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:16,902
Seriously?

343
00:24:18,617 --> 00:24:19,573
Yeah.

344
00:24:21,742 --> 00:24:23,168
A health condition.

345
00:24:23,680 --> 00:24:26,524
I only just found out he had a health condition.

346
00:24:32,995 --> 00:24:33,826
Ben.

347
00:24:35,582 --> 00:24:37,782
Things in the gang are really chaotic right now.

348
00:24:38,893 --> 00:24:42,626
There’s the succession issue, and I’m one of the candidates.

349
00:24:43,764 --> 00:24:46,017
There are others too—you understand, right?

350
00:24:47,635 --> 00:24:49,035
Are you okay?

351
00:24:55,302 --> 00:24:57,693
My family only has Suer.

352
00:25:03,555 --> 00:25:05,102
But now I also have you.

353
00:25:09,364 --> 00:25:10,466
I’m going now.

354
00:25:12,786 --> 00:25:15,702
When I finish everything, I’ll come back for you.

355
00:25:32,675 --> 00:25:33,902
Are you okay?

356
00:25:35,124 --> 00:25:36,168
I’m okay

357
00:25:38,915 --> 00:25:40,022
Are you sure?

358
00:25:46,964 --> 00:25:48,675
If I become the top leader,

359
00:25:49,137 --> 00:25:51,582
we’ll have to work really hard at first,

360
00:25:52,060 --> 00:25:55,008
to prove we’re worthy.

361
00:25:57,088 --> 00:25:58,431
And if you don’t get it?

362
00:26:01,902 --> 00:26:03,417
Then we become someone else’s subordinates.

363
00:26:05,262 --> 00:26:07,795
I don’t want that. Then you take it

364
00:26:09,222 --> 00:26:10,840
But if you don’t get it,

365
00:26:12,226 --> 00:26:14,035
we can start over on our own.

366
00:26:16,191 --> 00:26:17,777
Following Dad’s orders

367
00:26:17,871 --> 00:26:19,200
is still okay,

368
00:26:19,702 --> 00:26:21,106
because he respects you.

369
00:26:21,460 --> 00:26:23,420
But if I have to follow someone else,

370
00:26:23,795 --> 00:26:24,697
I won’t do it.

371
00:26:52,377 --> 00:26:54,146
I don’t know what to say.

372
00:26:59,302 --> 00:27:01,773
Dad wouldn’t want me to cry like this, right?

373
00:27:02,720 --> 00:27:03,711
Right?

374
00:27:06,897 --> 00:27:07,964
On the contrary,

375
00:27:09,106 --> 00:27:10,271
If I died,

376
00:27:12,275 --> 00:27:14,644
I wouldn’t want my father to cry either.

377
00:27:18,422 --> 00:27:20,844
You never loved me or my brother.

378
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:27,431
So what you get back

379
00:27:28,186 --> 00:27:29,724
isn’t love either.

380
00:27:37,900 --> 00:27:39,324
Do you have anything to say?

381
00:27:51,128 --> 00:27:53,271
I don’t hold any grudge against you anymore

382
00:27:54,315 --> 00:27:57,924
I’m not that kid anymore who craved your love

383
00:28:01,697 --> 00:28:03,182
Because now I have Singha.

384
00:28:05,946 --> 00:28:07,300
I have someone I love.

385
00:28:08,866 --> 00:28:10,333
That’s enough.

386
00:28:12,817 --> 00:28:13,995
Rest in peace.

387
00:28:16,528 --> 00:28:18,311
Singha. Suer.

388
00:28:18,853 --> 00:28:20,671
I need to talk to you.

389
00:28:27,675 --> 00:28:29,320
I’m sorry, my children,

390
00:28:29,795 --> 00:28:31,680
for everything that has happened.

391
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:33,875
I know saying this now

392
00:28:34,373 --> 00:28:36,835
won’t help.

393
00:28:37,280 --> 00:28:40,533
But the first and last thing I can do

394
00:28:41,817 --> 00:28:44,111
is to make Singha the top leader.

395
00:28:49,004 --> 00:28:50,284
How will you do that?

396
00:28:51,382 --> 00:28:54,955
I have allies who are branch leaders

397
00:28:55,302 --> 00:28:57,266
and they will support all of you.

398
00:28:59,360 --> 00:29:00,844
No matter what happens

399
00:29:01,288 --> 00:29:04,035
Singha will definitely become the top leader.

400
00:29:06,435 --> 00:29:07,720
And when that time comes,

401
00:29:08,613 --> 00:29:10,568
I'll going to disappear and start a new life.

402
00:29:17,860 --> 00:29:19,515
- I miss you.
- Hm?

403
00:29:20,226 --> 00:29:22,608
- Me?
- Suer.

404
00:29:23,835 --> 00:29:25,315
He has been gone for days.

405
00:29:25,448 --> 00:29:27,924
Well, why didn’t you just tell him?

406
00:29:28,426 --> 00:29:31,804
I did, but it’s not the same as seeing him in person.

407
00:29:34,417 --> 00:29:35,500
I feel lonely.

408
00:29:36,355 --> 00:29:37,942
You’re lonely because he’s not here.

409
00:29:38,671 --> 00:29:41,662
That’s what people in love are like.

410
00:29:42,115 --> 00:29:43,340
I’ll keep you company then.

411
00:29:43,577 --> 00:29:45,204
Since you’re lonely.

412
00:29:46,013 --> 00:29:48,511
So, how long are you going to study?

413
00:29:50,462 --> 00:29:53,426
I’ll keep studying as long as you’re here.

414
00:29:54,275 --> 00:29:56,150
Then I’ll study with you.

415
00:30:24,697 --> 00:30:25,675
What’s going on?

416
00:30:29,853 --> 00:30:30,897
Let’s go.

417
00:30:31,800 --> 00:30:34,248
Go where? I haven’t finished folding yet.

418
00:30:35,493 --> 00:30:36,640
You don’t have to anymore.

419
00:30:41,244 --> 00:30:43,600
Where are you going dressed like this?

420
00:30:46,060 --> 00:30:47,288
It’s

421
00:30:47,671 --> 00:30:49,884
the celebration party for Singha

422
00:30:50,457 --> 00:30:52,848
becoming the full boss of the mafia.

423
00:30:55,657 --> 00:30:56,533
Let’s go.

424
00:30:56,777 --> 00:30:57,546
Okay.

425
00:31:05,275 --> 00:31:06,577
Thank you, sir.

426
00:31:07,253 --> 00:31:08,084
Thank you.

427
00:31:09,031 --> 00:31:10,231
Thank you everyone.

428
00:31:10,720 --> 00:31:11,817
Cheers.

429
00:31:18,333 --> 00:31:19,380
How’s business going?

430
00:31:19,631 --> 00:31:22,253
Don’t be nervous. I'm here with you.

431
00:31:23,471 --> 00:31:24,057
Great.

432
00:31:31,653 --> 00:31:32,168
Oh.

433
00:31:32,955 --> 00:31:34,017
Hello.

434
00:31:36,168 --> 00:31:37,653
Congrats, bro.

435
00:31:39,448 --> 00:31:40,560
Thanks.

436
00:31:43,382 --> 00:31:44,804
Take your boyfriend for a walk.

437
00:31:47,640 --> 00:31:48,657
I’ll head out first then.

438
00:31:52,511 --> 00:31:53,071
Let’s go.

439
00:31:54,604 --> 00:31:55,573
Where are we walking to?

440
00:31:58,640 --> 00:31:59,702
So cute.

441
00:32:02,088 --> 00:32:04,862
Who was so suspicious of everyone before?

442
00:32:05,577 --> 00:32:06,800
I didn’t know!

443
00:32:07,337 --> 00:32:09,831
I have to be cautious with strangers.

444
00:32:10,942 --> 00:32:12,640
Yes, the first husband.

445
00:32:13,306 --> 00:32:14,493
First husband?

446
00:32:20,140 --> 00:32:21,835
I’m glad you’re back.

447
00:32:23,186 --> 00:32:24,573
Of course. I'm your man.

448
00:32:40,551 --> 00:32:41,551
Can I take it?

449
00:32:43,088 --> 00:32:44,035
Thank you.

450
00:32:47,471 --> 00:32:48,386
You like it?

451
00:32:50,200 --> 00:32:51,617
I’ve never tried it before.

452
00:32:52,448 --> 00:32:53,826
Go ahead.

453
00:32:54,297 --> 00:32:55,937
If you like it, just keep taking more.

454
00:32:57,071 --> 00:32:58,328
A booze buffet?

455
00:33:00,271 --> 00:33:01,764
There’s dessert too, want some?

456
00:33:03,164 --> 00:33:04,262
Can I really take it?

457
00:33:08,804 --> 00:33:10,044
Looks good.

458
00:33:10,648 --> 00:33:11,924
Hold this one for me please.

459
00:33:19,608 --> 00:33:20,751
What’s this called?

460
00:33:21,346 --> 00:33:22,511
Panna cotta.

461
00:33:23,582 --> 00:33:25,142
And this one?

462
00:33:27,350 --> 00:33:29,124
Maybe a tart, not sure.

463
00:33:32,906 --> 00:33:33,613
Tasty.

464
00:33:42,791 --> 00:33:44,217
Nice atmosphere, huh?

465
00:33:46,648 --> 00:33:47,977
I was thinking the same.

466
00:33:55,924 --> 00:33:56,608
Suer.

467
00:33:57,844 --> 00:33:59,208
I miss you.

468
00:34:00,368 --> 00:34:01,617
Haven’t seen you in days.

469
00:34:05,311 --> 00:34:06,808
I miss you too.

470
00:34:07,182 --> 00:34:08,515
I guess...

471
00:34:09,280 --> 00:34:10,902
I might miss you more.

472
00:35:29,533 --> 00:35:30,768
Are you okay?

473
00:35:31,533 --> 00:35:32,502
Yeah.

474
00:35:33,164 --> 00:35:34,180
I’m fine.

475
00:35:38,586 --> 00:35:39,662
Then let me?

476
00:36:24,702 --> 00:36:26,071
I love you.

477
00:36:27,435 --> 00:36:28,528
I love you too.

478
00:37:29,248 --> 00:37:30,040
Whoa.

479
00:37:32,191 --> 00:37:34,542
- Why are you surprised?
- Well…

480
00:37:35,373 --> 00:37:37,235
- You...
- What about me?

481
00:37:38,875 --> 00:37:40,360
You’re just really cute.

482
00:37:42,777 --> 00:37:44,062
It's normal.

483
00:37:54,937 --> 00:37:55,880
Suer.

484
00:37:56,408 --> 00:37:57,155
Hm?

485
00:37:58,013 --> 00:38:00,306
Do you think we’ll win tomorrow?

486
00:38:03,111 --> 00:38:04,293
Of course we will.

487
00:38:04,435 --> 00:38:05,720
With you here.

488
00:38:06,715 --> 00:38:07,835
That’s strange.

489
00:38:08,733 --> 00:38:10,542
You usually say

490
00:38:10,804 --> 00:38:12,235
"With me...".

491
00:38:16,791 --> 00:38:18,497
Then let’s change it.

492
00:38:19,106 --> 00:38:20,822
With us both,

493
00:38:21,435 --> 00:38:22,617
how could we lose?

494
00:38:27,244 --> 00:38:28,471
So confident.

495
00:38:33,893 --> 00:38:34,800
Hey.

496
00:38:36,600 --> 00:38:38,626
Hey, stop.

497
00:38:38,937 --> 00:38:40,284
Suer!

498
00:38:46,684 --> 00:38:48,013
Wow.

499
00:38:49,813 --> 00:38:51,275
Damn.

500
00:38:52,364 --> 00:38:54,262
This is the atmosphere I’ve always dreamed of.

501
00:38:54,355 --> 00:38:56,671
Damn, it feels like we’re back home.

502
00:38:56,777 --> 00:38:58,604
Where we’ve been practicing for three years.

503
00:38:58,751 --> 00:39:01,440
- Today’s the day. This is our breakout day, I’m telling you.
- We here to win the championship?

504
00:39:01,942 --> 00:39:03,480
- It’s been three years already?
- Yeah, three years already.

505
00:39:03,595 --> 00:39:04,368
I’m freaking excited.

506
00:39:04,871 --> 00:39:06,351
- You dreaming or what?
- Chill, it’s fine.

507
00:39:06,410 --> 00:39:10,124
Hey, focus up here. Everyone’s right here.
We’ve gotta give it our all today.

508
00:39:13,942 --> 00:39:15,524
Can you go with me first?

509
00:39:16,928 --> 00:39:18,760
Go where? It’s almost match time.

510
00:39:19,155 --> 00:39:21,293
- I’ve got a surprise for you.
- Another surprise? Seriously?

511
00:39:22,137 --> 00:39:24,940
- We’re about to compete and you still got surprises?
- Yeah, we’re about to compete, man.

512
00:39:25,235 --> 00:39:26,671
What surprise?

513
00:39:28,986 --> 00:39:31,177
Hey, we’re about to compete, you know. Hello?

514
00:39:31,595 --> 00:39:33,440
Damn, just go already.

515
00:39:33,693 --> 00:39:36,688
- Where’s North?
- I’m here, but I don’t wanna be here.

516
00:39:36,862 --> 00:39:40,400
I don’t wanna be here.

517
00:39:41,457 --> 00:39:42,942
Where are you taking me?

518
00:39:43,180 --> 00:39:44,075
You’ll see.

519
00:39:49,400 --> 00:39:50,906
Oh— Dan.

520
00:39:51,020 --> 00:39:53,835
- How did you get here?
- Surprise.

521
00:39:54,760 --> 00:39:57,497
- I miss you.
- I miss you too.

522
00:40:03,688 --> 00:40:05,920
You two planned this, didn’t you?

523
00:40:09,413 --> 00:40:12,013
At first I was gonna bring him after the match.

524
00:40:12,364 --> 00:40:16,044
But seeing how excited you were, I brought him earlier instead.
So you’d have more motivation.

525
00:40:17,560 --> 00:40:19,360
Yeah, thanks.

526
00:40:20,128 --> 00:40:21,173
Good luck, Duen.

527
00:40:21,422 --> 00:40:23,017
I will be cheering for you.

528
00:40:23,600 --> 00:40:24,986
Tiger, good luck too.

529
00:40:26,986 --> 00:40:28,893
Thanks for coming to see me, Dan.

530
00:40:43,155 --> 00:40:46,577
Hello everyone! Can I hear some noise?

531
00:40:48,662 --> 00:40:51,297
Are you ready to meet both teams? Are you ready?

532
00:40:51,524 --> 00:40:54,577
Let’s meet the contestants.

533
00:40:54,693 --> 00:40:58,186
Please welcome.

534
00:40:58,893 --> 00:41:03,644
Team fivevergangster, give them a cheer.

535
00:41:03,942 --> 00:41:07,955
And Team NOHOPE.

536
00:41:09,697 --> 00:41:14,240
Who’s cheering for NOHOPE? Let me hear you!

537
00:41:14,982 --> 00:41:18,675
Who’s cheering for fivevergangster? Let me hear you!

538
00:41:21,280 --> 00:41:22,413
Thank you very much.

539
00:41:22,733 --> 00:41:26,488
Alright, let’s see which team will be champion this year.

540
00:41:26,928 --> 00:41:30,795
No need to waste time, let’s go.

541
00:41:33,404 --> 00:41:35,010
Thank you.

542
00:41:35,920 --> 00:41:38,088
Alright, get ready.

543
00:41:42,271 --> 00:41:43,564
Come on, everyone.

544
00:41:46,408 --> 00:41:49,280
Take positions in the bushes.

545
00:41:49,488 --> 00:41:52,364
Okay.

546
00:41:52,475 --> 00:41:54,500
Alright?

547
00:41:55,448 --> 00:41:58,355
Nice, nice.

548
00:41:58,866 --> 00:42:00,120
Yes!

549
00:42:03,395 --> 00:42:06,862
Follow me.

550
00:42:06,937 --> 00:42:08,848
Cover them.

551
00:42:09,226 --> 00:42:12,266
Mid lane, North!

552
00:42:12,364 --> 00:42:13,471
I’m coming.

553
00:42:13,697 --> 00:42:16,160
Let’s go.

554
00:42:16,400 --> 00:42:20,666
Hurry!

555
00:42:25,940 --> 00:42:30,977
Got it!
Yay!

556
00:42:40,880 --> 00:42:42,600
Champion!

557
00:42:44,035 --> 00:42:46,640
Congratulations to today’s champions,

558
00:42:46,764 --> 00:42:48,862
NOHOPE.

559
00:42:51,942 --> 00:42:54,053
Applause!

560
00:42:58,973 --> 00:43:00,586
Let’s do an interview.

561
00:43:00,720 --> 00:43:03,084
How do you feel about winning today?

562
00:43:03,626 --> 00:43:05,400
I feel really happy.

563
00:43:05,835 --> 00:43:07,435
How long did you train as a team?

564
00:43:07,853 --> 00:43:10,751
A long time, because we usually already play this game.

565
00:43:10,977 --> 00:43:13,364
How does it feel to represent your university…

566
00:43:13,453 --> 00:43:16,871
…and compete in other tournaments?

567
00:43:16,980 --> 00:43:19,026
We’ll do our best.

568
00:43:20,120 --> 00:43:23,173
Thank you. Give it up for NOHOPE!

569
00:43:25,257 --> 00:43:26,417
My friends, my friends!

570
00:43:26,511 --> 00:43:30,600
NOHOPE! NOHOPE!

571
00:43:32,453 --> 00:43:35,328
Cheers.

572
00:43:35,497 --> 00:43:37,177
Congratulations.

573
00:43:37,257 --> 00:43:38,031
Yeah.

574
00:43:40,400 --> 00:43:42,666
At first I thought you were just playing around.

575
00:43:42,764 --> 00:43:44,995
Damn, you actually became the university team.

576
00:43:45,782 --> 00:43:47,697
I was so damn happy when we won.

577
00:43:47,720 --> 00:43:51,044
Great job, captain.

578
00:43:51,137 --> 00:43:53,902
So cool man.

579
00:43:53,960 --> 00:43:55,542
Alright, alright.

580
00:43:55,795 --> 00:43:57,213
There’s still more good news

581
00:43:57,520 --> 00:43:58,635
What is it?

582
00:43:59,480 --> 00:44:04,666
Congratulations to the new couple.

583
00:44:10,182 --> 00:44:11,626
Finally get together already.

584
00:44:11,860 --> 00:44:13,568
I’ve been rooting for you forever.

585
00:44:14,080 --> 00:44:15,266
Thanks, man.

586
00:44:15,568 --> 00:44:19,755
Thanks, Nao. Without him, we would’ve stopped being friends long ago.

587
00:44:20,040 --> 00:44:21,084
Thank you, Nao.

588
00:44:21,302 --> 00:44:25,626
You’re honestly the best friend ever.

589
00:44:25,746 --> 00:44:27,502
I know that.

590
00:44:27,622 --> 00:44:31,137
- Wow, no chill at all.
- Hey, wait, what about me?

591
00:44:31,337 --> 00:44:32,164
Why?

592
00:44:32,413 --> 00:44:33,831
I was the one who tell him to made the call.

593
00:44:34,053 --> 00:44:36,293
He's literally the starter here.

594
00:44:36,475 --> 00:44:40,764
- You too, then.
- Thank you, bro.

595
00:44:40,893 --> 00:44:43,666
So now it’s just Field and Get left.

596
00:44:44,235 --> 00:44:46,520
- Oops.
- I’ve got someone I’m talking to.

597
00:44:46,786 --> 00:44:49,724
Sure, like anyone would want you.

598
00:44:49,973 --> 00:44:51,684
- North!
- Hey, hey.

599
00:44:52,177 --> 00:44:55,222
- Chill out.
- I didn’t do anything.

600
00:44:55,453 --> 00:44:57,706
Like Field, huh?

601
00:44:59,551 --> 00:45:00,564
What did I do this time?

602
00:45:01,253 --> 00:45:03,262
You’re just someone she’s talking to.

603
00:45:03,693 --> 00:45:07,804
You try to flirt with her, but in the end you get played
and then dumped.

604
00:45:07,911 --> 00:45:10,248
And you’re just a backup option.

605
00:45:10,520 --> 00:45:12,675
That hurts deep.

606
00:45:12,746 --> 00:45:15,320
It really hurts.

607
00:45:15,506 --> 00:45:16,795
It hurts so bad.

608
00:45:17,408 --> 00:45:19,444
Hey, why don’t you two try dating?

609
00:45:19,675 --> 00:45:21,924
Hey!

610
00:45:26,262 --> 00:45:27,515
Nah, better not.

611
00:45:27,697 --> 00:45:30,560
Damn, I was actually rooting for you two.

612
00:45:30,604 --> 00:45:32,120
Oh well.

613
00:45:32,220 --> 00:45:34,128
But I saw you stick your tongue out just now.

614
00:45:36,302 --> 00:45:37,880
It was lightning.

615
00:45:40,168 --> 00:45:43,980
- It was a flash!
- Okay, cheers—

616
00:45:44,088 --> 00:45:45,493
Cheers, cheers!

617
00:45:45,617 --> 00:45:46,822
Where’s the alcohol?

618
00:45:49,760 --> 00:45:50,564
Suer.

619
00:45:51,977 --> 00:45:54,262
I talked to Dan. We’re going home soon.

620
00:45:54,457 --> 00:45:56,391
Come home with me too.

621
00:45:56,742 --> 00:45:58,093
So we can tell Mom about us.

622
00:46:02,577 --> 00:46:03,288
Hey.

623
00:46:03,911 --> 00:46:05,671
You’re telling Aunt Maew about us?

624
00:46:06,884 --> 00:46:07,808
Yeah.

625
00:46:08,262 --> 00:46:09,546
I think I’m ready now.

626
00:46:11,420 --> 00:46:13,817
Sorry for making you wait so long.

627
00:46:16,986 --> 00:46:18,244
It’s okay.

628
00:46:18,737 --> 00:46:19,608
But…

629
00:46:20,826 --> 00:46:22,177
I’m kind of nervous.

630
00:46:22,448 --> 00:46:24,288
I haven’t seen Aunt Maew in so long.

631
00:46:24,586 --> 00:46:25,675
It’s okay.

632
00:46:26,182 --> 00:46:27,466
Come on.

633
00:46:30,546 --> 00:46:31,648
Shall we toast?

634
00:46:34,995 --> 00:46:36,582
Let’s toast.

635
00:46:36,737 --> 00:46:39,284
Cheers, cheers.

636
00:46:39,444 --> 00:46:41,351
Cheers.

637
00:46:46,791 --> 00:46:47,520
Mom.

638
00:46:50,568 --> 00:46:51,697
Dan, Duen.

639
00:46:52,000 --> 00:46:53,462
I miss you so much, kids.

640
00:46:53,528 --> 00:46:56,137
- How have you been?
- I miss you too.

641
00:46:58,128 --> 00:47:00,280
It’s been so long since we saw each other.

642
00:47:02,893 --> 00:47:04,546
Can I get a hug too?

643
00:47:04,711 --> 00:47:07,142
Of course, Tiger, come here.

644
00:47:11,608 --> 00:47:13,035
You’re not opening the shop today?

645
00:47:15,124 --> 00:47:19,320
Yesterday was really busy, I was exhausted,
so I took a day off.

646
00:47:20,231 --> 00:47:23,160
Good idea. You shouldn’t overwork yourself.

647
00:47:24,297 --> 00:47:26,737
Have you eaten yet?

648
00:47:27,088 --> 00:47:30,026
Not yet, Mom. I’m starving.

649
00:47:30,217 --> 00:47:32,008
I miss your cooking the most.

650
00:47:32,177 --> 00:47:34,186
Tiger cooks for you every day.

651
00:47:34,440 --> 00:47:36,400
But it’s not the same as yours.

652
00:47:38,426 --> 00:47:40,506
How could it be the same as Mom’s cooking?

653
00:47:40,893 --> 00:47:42,804
Your cooking is the best in the world.

654
00:47:43,173 --> 00:47:46,413
Wait, didn’t you say I was your mom top student?

655
00:47:49,102 --> 00:47:50,137
Wait…

656
00:47:52,391 --> 00:47:53,577
What is going on here?

657
00:47:53,711 --> 00:47:55,622
Hey—hey, you two…

658
00:48:15,875 --> 00:48:18,524
We’re dating, Mom.

659
00:48:25,466 --> 00:48:28,097
I knew it.

660
00:48:28,360 --> 00:48:31,284
What do you mean you knew it? You already knew?

661
00:48:31,671 --> 00:48:35,204
I’ve suspected it for a long time.
This is your mom, you know.

662
00:48:35,995 --> 00:48:38,622
I’ve had my eye on you two the whole time.

663
00:48:39,564 --> 00:48:40,968
Right, Duen?

664
00:48:41,751 --> 00:48:43,084
Yeah.

665
00:48:44,786 --> 00:48:45,613
Hey.

666
00:48:45,888 --> 00:48:47,800
How did you end up dating Tiger?

667
00:48:48,902 --> 00:48:50,822
Me? Chase him?

668
00:48:51,400 --> 00:48:52,324
Yeah.

669
00:48:55,364 --> 00:48:56,346
What?

670
00:48:57,164 --> 00:48:58,662
No?

671
00:48:59,777 --> 00:49:01,160
Not like that?

672
00:49:03,853 --> 00:49:06,164
So you’ve liked Duen since high school?

673
00:49:08,608 --> 00:49:11,533
So I misunderstood the whole time?

674
00:49:12,066 --> 00:49:15,742
Yes. I’ve liked him since high school.

675
00:49:16,373 --> 00:49:17,315
Oh.

676
00:49:17,991 --> 00:49:19,262
What about you, Duen?

677
00:49:19,795 --> 00:49:22,631
I only realized my feelings when Suer confessed.

678
00:49:23,031 --> 00:49:26,306
I had no idea he liked me before that.

679
00:49:27,791 --> 00:49:29,700
Six years, huh.

680
00:49:31,208 --> 00:49:31,986
Yeah.

681
00:49:33,031 --> 00:49:35,440
You really didn’t notice at all?

682
00:49:35,657 --> 00:49:37,124
Not at all, Mom.

683
00:49:37,346 --> 00:49:39,777
Suer was just very sneaky.

684
00:49:41,088 --> 00:49:43,410
It’s your own fault for not noticing.

685
00:49:43,662 --> 00:49:45,920
Even I could tell.

686
00:49:46,106 --> 00:49:46,955
Hey.

687
00:49:47,937 --> 00:49:48,946
Fine.

688
00:49:49,777 --> 00:49:52,795
Anyway, I’m really happy for you both.

689
00:49:53,066 --> 00:49:54,764
That you’re together.

690
00:49:55,764 --> 00:49:57,800
I’m sure Tiger

691
00:49:58,008 --> 00:49:59,240
will take good care of you.

692
00:49:59,426 --> 00:50:01,475
And love you very much.

693
00:50:02,062 --> 00:50:03,671
And you too, Duen.

694
00:50:04,977 --> 00:50:05,711
Yes, Mom.

695
00:50:07,324 --> 00:50:11,635
Aww, you’re really good at being sweet, aren’t you?

696
00:50:12,195 --> 00:50:13,377
Thank you, Aunt Maew.

697
00:50:13,675 --> 00:50:15,022
for letting me stay with you.

698
00:50:16,880 --> 00:50:18,706
I’ve wanted to say this for a long time.

699
00:50:19,413 --> 00:50:21,208
I’ve been really happy all this time.

700
00:50:26,364 --> 00:50:28,115
You can call me Mom.

701
00:50:29,786 --> 00:50:31,782
- Right?
- Yes, Mom

702
00:50:31,951 --> 00:50:34,471
Come on, let's eat.

703
00:50:34,946 --> 00:50:38,866
Then eat a lot, my son-in-law.

704
00:50:38,942 --> 00:50:41,226
- Big portions for you.
- Thank you.

705
00:50:41,271 --> 00:50:43,004
Son-in-law?

706
00:50:43,150 --> 00:50:46,551
He’s my son-in-law. What else would I call him?

707
00:50:47,368 --> 00:50:49,186
Wait a second.

708
00:50:50,066 --> 00:50:52,404
I remember back in middle school,

709
00:50:52,653 --> 00:50:55,880
you said there was this handsome football captain...

710
00:50:56,288 --> 00:50:58,493
- Tiger, right?
- That’s right, Mom.

711
00:50:58,613 --> 00:51:00,631
You used to talk about him every night.

712
00:51:00,826 --> 00:51:03,320
Right? Ahhh.

713
00:51:03,822 --> 00:51:05,040
I was handsome?

714
00:51:06,075 --> 00:51:08,004
So I wasn’t wrong after all.

715
00:51:08,182 --> 00:51:09,380
No.

716
00:51:09,960 --> 00:51:11,088
What?

717
00:51:11,275 --> 00:51:12,720
Aha, got you.

718
00:51:13,004 --> 00:51:13,884
Mom.

719
00:51:24,648 --> 00:51:25,457
Hey.

720
00:51:26,404 --> 00:51:29,493
Shall we go walk around our old school?

721
00:51:30,871 --> 00:51:31,715
Sure.

722
00:51:31,991 --> 00:51:34,084
I wonder how much it’s changed.

723
00:51:37,320 --> 00:51:38,000
Huh.

724
00:51:38,780 --> 00:51:39,760
It’s still the same.

725
00:51:40,302 --> 00:51:41,360
Yeah.

726
00:51:43,786 --> 00:51:45,417
I miss the football field.

727
00:51:46,620 --> 00:51:48,186
The one you couldn’t score on?

728
00:51:48,680 --> 00:51:51,626
What? I could score!

729
00:51:52,560 --> 00:51:55,408
Score? I gave you so many passes, you missed so many shots.

730
00:51:55,951 --> 00:51:57,791
You were the one passing badly.

731
00:51:58,315 --> 00:52:00,551
We should really watch the footage again.

732
00:52:01,093 --> 00:52:02,604
How many years has it been?

733
00:52:04,991 --> 00:52:06,257
Three?

734
00:52:06,560 --> 00:52:07,831
I thought it was ten.

735
00:52:08,302 --> 00:52:09,533
So long ago.

736
00:52:10,140 --> 00:52:11,337
Come on, let’s go to the field.

737
00:52:18,284 --> 00:52:19,115
Hey.

738
00:52:20,591 --> 00:52:21,900
This is the spot

739
00:52:22,217 --> 00:52:23,644
where we first met, right?

740
00:52:26,186 --> 00:52:26,911
Yes.

741
00:52:27,271 --> 00:52:30,822
- But when we first met, you punched me.
- Serves you right.

742
00:52:31,320 --> 00:52:35,457
You teased my mom’s name,
so you can hit me back.

743
00:52:42,395 --> 00:52:45,404
Hey, not so tough, huh?

744
00:52:46,604 --> 00:52:47,768
Let me punch you?

745
00:52:48,075 --> 00:52:49,684
I'd rather punch myself.

746
00:52:50,564 --> 00:52:53,364
- That’s overacting.
- Not really.

747
00:52:53,911 --> 00:52:55,720
Because I really like you a lot.

748
00:52:56,728 --> 00:52:57,813
Just like?

749
00:52:59,137 --> 00:53:01,373
I thought it was love.

750
00:53:02,120 --> 00:53:04,164
Turns out I already love you.

751
00:53:04,284 --> 00:53:05,942
What should I do?

752
00:53:08,777 --> 00:53:11,822
I love you so much right now.

753
00:53:11,937 --> 00:53:13,026
Hmm, these days...

754
00:53:14,062 --> 00:53:15,200
Yeah.

755
00:53:19,928 --> 00:53:21,422
Where do you want to go next?

756
00:53:21,946 --> 00:53:23,248
Where?

757
00:53:27,217 --> 00:53:28,226
I don’t want to go anywhere.

758
00:53:30,075 --> 00:53:32,973
Then can you go somewhere with me?

759
00:53:34,062 --> 00:53:35,702
- Where?
- Not telling.

760
00:53:36,180 --> 00:53:39,213
- If you don’t tell me, I’m not going.
- Come on.

761
00:53:39,266 --> 00:53:40,995
Tell me first.

762
00:54:00,195 --> 00:54:01,844
Not many people here, like always.

763
00:54:04,302 --> 00:54:06,084
You said to bring your boyfriend.

764
00:54:07,780 --> 00:54:09,195
I brought him for real now.

765
00:54:13,435 --> 00:54:14,413
Um.

766
00:54:14,826 --> 00:54:15,680
Yeah, it’s true.

767
00:54:19,231 --> 00:54:20,604
Thinking about the past, huh.

768
00:54:20,977 --> 00:54:24,102
When we were stressed, we always came here.

769
00:54:27,380 --> 00:54:28,871
It felt like this place was ours.

770
00:54:40,648 --> 00:54:41,613
Duennao.

771
00:54:46,351 --> 00:54:47,737
I love you so much.

772
00:54:53,666 --> 00:54:54,724
I love you too.

773
00:55:02,595 --> 00:55:04,715
Thank you for coming into my life.

774
00:55:06,702 --> 00:55:07,875
You are like

775
00:55:10,226 --> 00:55:11,888
my whole world.

776
00:55:13,284 --> 00:55:14,573
Since I have you,

777
00:55:15,008 --> 00:55:17,164
I’ve been so happy.

778
00:55:21,164 --> 00:55:22,600
Me too.

779
00:55:24,720 --> 00:55:27,173
Thank you for not giving up for 6 years.

780
00:55:31,031 --> 00:55:32,488
Can you stay...

781
00:55:34,680 --> 00:55:36,746
and keep making each other smile forever?

782
00:55:40,017 --> 00:55:40,737
Ok.
